05 May 2020 14:59






This hits a really good middle-point between dream logic and internal consistency. I didn't find it particularly creepy or scary, but I think it works well that way because it makes the bizarreness of it all stick out more. The fact that it feels, for a lack of better word, non-scary makes the weirdness and mystery of it more interesting. What encapsulates this best is the fact that the weird stuff that happens in the mill isn't overtly deadly or dangerous and that the company will just fire you rather than kill you. It makes whatever weird shit going on more compelling and imaginative than just .

My only real criticism is the reaction at the end. Suddenly screaming and running while screaming feels like something out of a cartoon, not a realistic human reaction (it might be real, but the way it reads is cartoonish). Changing the writing so that the panic reactions feels more natural would make the ending better.

Either way, I really like the weird ass shit that's going on here, +1







